# ============================================================
# Setup Instructions for Admin Analytics
# ============================================================

# 1. Generate NEXTAUTH_SECRET:
#    Run one of these commands in your terminal:
#    - openssl rand -base64 32
#    - node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('base64'))"
#
# 2. Set your admin credentials:
#    - ADMIN_EMAIL: Email you'll use to log in to /admin
#    - ADMIN_PASSWORD: Secure password (min 12 characters recommended)
#
# 3. Update NEXTAUTH_URL for production:
#    - Development: http://localhost:3000
#    - Production: https://xplife.app
#
# 4. Run database migration:
#    - Open Supabase Dashboard
#    - Go to SQL Editor
#    - Paste contents of supabase/analytics-migration.sql
#    - Execute the migration
#
# 5. Verify setup:
#    - npm run dev
#    - Visit http://localhost:3000/admin
#    - Should redirect to /admin/login
#    - Log in with your credentials
#    - Dashboard should load with analytics data

# ============================================================
# Security Reminders
# ============================================================
# - Never commit .env.local to git (already in .gitignore)
# - Use strong passwords (12+ characters, mixed case, numbers, symbols)
# - Rotate NEXTAUTH_SECRET periodically in production
# - Keep SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY secret (never expose to client)
# - Use environment variables in Vercel for production deployment
